AB  - The primary purpose of this paper is to highlight how companies manage their resources and what factors determine their profitability and financial stability. The methodology consisted of selecting the first 1,000 companies in the HoReCa sector, distributed at the county level (41 counties plus Bucharest), based on turnover, which have at least one employee and a turnover greater than 2,000 lei. During the database cleaning stage, we eliminated companies that lacked all the necessary information, those with erroneous data and those that had no activity during the analyzed period (2020-2024), as this was the most recent data available at the time of database querying. We followed the calculation and interpretation of a set of indicators, starting with profitability indicators, liquidity indicators, financial structure indicators, and, last but not least, productivity indicators. The results obtained from the investigation of these indicators found that profitability is relatively low, but specific to the analyzed sector, the fact that in the HoReCa sector we encounter an uneven situation, with a limited number of large, profitable companies and on the other hand, several companies that have low profitability or even sometimes record losses. Regarding labor productivity, the results showed that an increase in the degree of digitization and automation of specific processes, along with a prudent financing policy, is necessary. Notably, some companies face difficulties in covering their current debts and do not consistently have sufficient liquid resources. The conclusions took into account the impact on specific investments and on adjusting the degree of indebtedness, through correct debt management and resource optimization.
